                    <span>This is a well-written, carefully organized book that belongs on desks across America!  Topics covered include organizing before writing, overcoming writer's block, suiting letters to complex situations, and using  grammar and punctuation properly.  If I had to provide one criticism, it  would only be that the book is too short!  As a reader, I didn't tire of  the useful sample letters and would have happily read more and more.  A  great reference for the tentative writer and a good refresher for seasoned  writers, as well.</span>
                  
              
